HEADWORD: Willying
<hw>Wil"ly*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The process of cleansing wool,
cotton, or the like, with a willy, or willow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Willying machine</b></col>. <cd>Same as 1st
<er>Willow</er>, 2.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Willy nilly</ent>⟦br⟧
